      "content": "redefining yourself feels like a joke. there is no \"authentic\" version of me left. the person people respected was just a byproduct of the work, and without the work, there is literally nothing. it's like looking in a mirror and seeing a blank space. i'm just tired of the noise of pretending. it feels like i'm just occupying space that doesn't belong to me anymore. doesn't it just feel more honest to just... let the performance end?",
